      "option": 1,
      "citation": "Cf. Ps 43 (42):1–2",
      "text": "Give me justice, O God,\nand plead my cause against a nation that is faithless.\nFrom the deceitful and cunning rescue me,\nfor you, O God, are my strength."
    },
    {
      "type": "communion",
      "option": 1,
      "citation": "For Jn 12:24 (Grain of Wheat)",
      "text": "Amen, Amen I say to you: Unless a grain of wheat\nfalls to the ground and dies, it remains a single grain.\nBut if it dies, it bears much fruit."
    }
